.TH "rdma_replace_ah_attr" 9 "rdma_replace_ah_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_replace_ah_attr \- Replace valid ah_attr with new new one.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rdma_replace_ah_attr
.BI "(struct rdma_ah_attr *old "  ","
.BI "const struct rdma_ah_attr *new "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "old" 12
Pointer to existing ah_attr which needs to be replaced.
old is assumed to be valid or zero'd
.IP "new" 12
Pointer to the new ah_attr.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBrdma_replace_ah_attr\fP first releases any reference in the old ah_attr if
old the ah_attr is valid; after that it copies the new attribute and holds
the reference to the replaced ah_attr.
